Add an **Algorithm Layer** between ContextFrame and Daemon execution.

# MONEYBIN ARTIFACT

## Algorithmic Thinking Layer v1.0

### Purpose

The Algorithmic Thinking Layer converts Pantheon’s natural-language doctrine into repeatable reasoning procedures.

Pantheon already defines frames, daemons, invariants, and narrative operators.

This layer adds the missing bridge:

> frame → procedure → execution → audit

The goal is not to remove creativity.

The goal is to make creativity inspectable, repeatable, and testable.

---

## Core Principle

A frame tells the system **how to see**.

An algorithm tells the system **what to do next**.

Pantheon requires both.

```text
ContextFrame
    ↓
Algorithm Selector
    ↓
Reasoning Procedure
    ↓
Daemon Execution
    ↓
Ledgered Result
```

---

